{"id": 4155, "title": "Ticket #4155: Improve handling of coresize for jobs", "description": "<blockquote>\nIn the kernel interface for setting limits on core file size (setrlimit()), the special value RLIM_INFINITY means unlimited. It's always unsigned, but its value and type size vary between platforms. It's not always -1 cast to an unsigned type. Also, now that <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAds\" title=\"Class Ads\">ClassAds</a></span> support 64-bit integers, we should recognize large coresize values.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Jan-29 14:51</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ae2863381bfd12b50d6ee3fac94095f3773a0c17\">[39256]</a></span>: minor edit to 8.1.4 version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4155\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4155'); return false;\" title=\"Improve handling of coresize for jobs\">#4155</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Jan-14 14:01</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/a12c5a7349264ee885e910a04e62ad96cfbf88cb\">[39153]</a></span>: Docs for improving job coresize handling. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4155\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4155'); return false;\" title=\"Improve handling of coresize for jobs\">#4155</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Jan-14 13:58</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/b9e712eaf3c0ffd3776f6efce02ffc7f513097ec\">[39152]</a></span>: Improve handling of coresize for jobs. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4155\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4155'); return false;\" title=\"Improve handling of coresize for jobs\">#4155</a></span> Use RLIM_INIFINITY when we want an unlimited coresize for a job. On Darwin and Solaris, RLIM_INFINITY isn't (unsigned long)-1, so be more careful with negatives values for <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=CoreSize\" title=\"Core Size\">CoreSize</a></span> in the job ad. Also, handle <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=CoreSize\" title=\"Core Size\">CoreSize</a></span> values larger than 32 bits.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2014-Jan-14 14:03", "status": "resolved", "created": "2014-Jan-14 13:29", "fixed_version": "2014-Jan-14 13:29", "broken_version": "v080000", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "DaemonsExecNode", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "#1425", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}